start.label: good deed is its own reward
get out what one puts in

examples.en: She wanted to reward the cleaners for their efforts.
Love is the reward for love.
We rewarded him for finding our lost dog.
A reward of $20,000 has been offered.
Success brings its own rewards.
The finder usually receives a reward.
To reward high performance, use bonuses.
The reward spurred them to work harder.
Hard work brings its own rewards.
She rewarded herself by buying a new pair of shoes.
The police are offering a reward for any information.
It is important to reward good behaviour.
A magnificent view rewards the traveller.
Most people will respond to the reward of money.
Even young children worked assiduously for a reward.
He thinks that to propose a reward for virtue is to render virtue impossible.
She began to reap (=get) the rewards of all her hard work.
The reward money was an unexpected dividend for our good deed.
Righteous behavior is its own reward.
$10,000 is a goodly reward to offer for a missing wedding ring.
Virtuous behavior is its own reward.
The scout was rewarded for courageous action.
The job is difficult, but the financial rewards are great.
The paper put up a reward for information on the murder.
The club's directors rewarded him with a free season ticket.
They took to the water intent on netting the $250,000 offered reward.
Any one of that crush would do murder for no more than 500 dollars reward.
Members will receive a discount in reward for getting friends or family to join.
The reward consisted in three stone busts of Hermes.
Several of the parents were giving their children rewards for passing exams.
